                <h2>APPENDIX 2 - APPROPRIATE TECHNICAL AND ORGANISATIONAL MEASURES IMPLEMENTED</h2>

                <p>The following technical and organisational measures are implemented by Hook0 in order to protect Personal Data against accidental or unlawful destruction, loss, alteration, unauthorized disclosure or access to Personal Data transmitted, stored or otherwise processed:</p>

                <h3>Infrastructure Security (managed by Clever Cloud SAS)</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Application hosted on Clever Cloud SAS infrastructure in France (EU);</li>
                    <li>Database encryption at rest (managed by Clever Cloud);</li>
                    <li>TLS 1.2+ encryption for all data in transit (rustls);</li>
                    <li>Automated daily backups with 30-day retention;</li>
                    <li>DDoS protection via Cloudflare;</li>
                    <li>Physical access controls for datacenter facilities are delegated to Clever Cloud SAS in accordance with their ISO 27001-certified security programme.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Application Security</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Password hashing with Argon2 (state-of-the-art);</li>
                    <li>Capability-based authorization tokens (Biscuit);</li>
                    <li>Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) for platform access;</li>
                    <li>Automatic session expiration.</li>
                </ul>
                <p><strong>Note on multi-factor authentication (MFA):</strong> MFA is enforced for all infrastructure access (Clever Cloud, GitLab, Stripe). MFA for individual Hook0 user accounts is not yet implemented at the application level and is planned for a future release.</p>

                <h3>Development Security</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>All code changes require peer review via merge requests;</li>
                    <li>Automated CI/CD pipeline including:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Static Application Security Testing (SAST);</li>
                            <li>Dynamic Application Security Testing (DAST);</li>
                            <li>Container scanning (Trivy);</li>
                            <li>Dependency vulnerability scanning (osv-scanner);</li>
                            <li>Secret detection.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li>Strict code linting (Clippy with warnings-as-errors).</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Monitoring and Incident Response</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Error tracking via Sentry;</li>
                    <li>Distributed tracing via OpenTelemetry;</li>
                    <li>Uptime monitoring via BetterUptime with public status page;</li>
                    <li>Responsible disclosure policy with PGP-secured reporting.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Organisational Measures</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Information classification policy (Public, Internal, Confidential, Sensitive);</li>
                    <li>NDAs required for all personnel;</li>
                    <li>Security awareness practices;</li>
                    <li>Need-to-know access principle;</li>
                    <li>MFA enforced for infrastructure access (Clever Cloud, GitLab, Stripe);</li>
                    <li>Penetration testing conducted annually or after major architectural changes.</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Data Retention</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Webhook event data: per customer plan (7–30 days);</li>
                    <li>Account data: duration of contract plus 30 days;</li>
                    <li>Billing records: 10 years (French tax law);</li>
                    <li>Logs: 30 days minimum.</li>
                </ul>

